<i>♪ One, two ♪</i>

03:44.834 --> 03:46.834
<i>- ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪</i>

03:46.875 --> 03:48.041
<i>- ♪ One, two, three, four! ♪</i>

03:50.375 --> 03:56.000
♪

03:56.041 --> 03:57.959
- What're you doing?

03:58.000 --> 03:59.625
- Sweating out the germs.

03:59.667 --> 04:01.917
- I think you're

03:59.667 --> 04:01.917
just making 'em angry.

04:01.959 --> 04:05.375
- There.

04:01.959 --> 04:05.375
I feel better already.

04:05.417 --> 04:10.959
Also, I feel...

04:05.417 --> 04:10.959
really dizzy.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.917
- Well, look on the bright side,

04:11.000 --> 04:13.917
at least we get

04:11.000 --> 04:13.917
to go to the museum.

04:13.959 --> 04:17.041
We'll tell you all about it.

04:17.083 --> 04:19.667
[panting]

04:17.083 --> 04:19.667
Okay,

04:19.709 --> 04:22.542
if I can't kick it,

04:19.709 --> 04:22.542
I'm gonna hide it.

04:22.583 --> 04:25.583
Look, I am not missing

04:22.583 --> 04:25.583
that epic moment.

04:25.625 --> 04:28.458
Ricky, you have to help me

04:25.625 --> 04:28.458
hide this from Mom and Dad.

04:28.500 --> 04:32.083
- Why me?

04:28.500 --> 04:32.083
- Well, we all know you've been

04:28.500 --> 04:32.083
faking well for years

04:32.125 --> 04:33.875
so you never have

04:32.125 --> 04:33.875
to miss a day at school.

04:33.917 --> 04:36.458
- Well, it is true

04:33.917 --> 04:36.458
that my attendance is perfect.

04:36.500 --> 04:39.750
Whoo-whoo!

04:39.792 --> 04:41.709
But I'm sorry,

04:39.792 --> 04:41.709
I've worked too long

04:41.750 --> 04:43.834
and too hard mastering

04:41.750 --> 04:43.834
my "faking well" techniques

04:43.875 --> 04:46.625
to share them with you.

04:46.667 --> 04:48.500
- Well, then I'm sorry

04:48.542 --> 04:50.667
because you're gonna have

04:48.542 --> 04:50.667
to miss the trip too.

04:50.709 --> 04:52.542
- What do you mean?

04:50.709 --> 04:52.542
I'm going.

04:52.583 --> 04:54.917
- Not if you're sick.

04:52.583 --> 04:54.917
- But I'm not sick.

04:54.959 --> 04:57.041
- Yet.

04:57.083 --> 05:01.291
I feel a very wet sneeze coming

04:57.083 --> 05:01.291
with your name on it.

05:01.333 --> 05:03.709
- Make it as wet as you want.

05:01.333 --> 05:03.709
It won't matter.

05:03.750 --> 05:06.333
I know how to fake being well.

05:06.375 --> 05:08.250
- [sighs]

05:06.375 --> 05:08.250
Fine.

05:08.291 --> 05:12.166
I really didn't want

05:08.291 --> 05:12.166
to have to do this, but...

05:12.208 --> 05:13.959
I'm playing my Quad Card.

05:14.000 --> 05:15.250
[all gasp]

05:15.291 --> 05:17.333
- Yeah, that's right,

05:15.291 --> 05:17.333
and as we all know,

05:17.375 --> 05:19.041
when one of us plays their card,

05:19.083 --> 05:20.834
the other three

05:19.083 --> 05:20.834
have to do what we say,

05:20.875 --> 05:22.250
no questions asked.

05:22.291 --> 05:24.458
- You had your Quad Card

05:22.291 --> 05:24.458
in your pajamas?

05:24.500 --> 05:26.333
- No questions asked!

05:26.375 --> 05:29.166
- Dawn, you only get

05:26.375 --> 05:29.166
one Quad Card a year.

05:29.208 --> 05:31.333
Are you sure this is

05:29.208 --> 05:31.333
what you want to use it for?

05:31.375 --> 05:33.917
- Question!

05:35.125 --> 05:36.875
- Fine, then let the record show

05:36.917 --> 05:38.959
that one Dawn Abigail Harper

05:39.000 --> 05:41.125
has played her Quad Card

05:39.000 --> 05:41.125
for the year

05:41.166 --> 05:43.750
at 8:35 a.m. on this,

05:43.792 --> 05:46.083
the fifth day of the month.

05:46.125 --> 05:47.291
Nicky, did you get that?

05:47.333 --> 05:50.291
- It is gotten.

05:50.333 --> 05:52.291
- You had all that

05:50.333 --> 05:52.291
in your pajamas?

05:52.333 --> 05:54.458
- No questions asked.

05:54.500 --> 05:57.417
[upbeat music]

05:59.417 --> 06:01.125
- [grunts]

05:59.417 --> 06:01.125
- [sneezes]

06:01.166 --> 06:03.291
- Oh, bless you.

06:07.208 --> 06:08.417
- How's it coming

06:07.208 --> 06:08.417
with the drink?

06:08.458 --> 06:11.166
- Welcome to

06:08.458 --> 06:11.166
Ricky's Faking Well Seminar.

06:11.208 --> 06:12.375
Step one:

06:12.417 --> 06:15.291
Drink...

06:15.333 --> 06:17.250
that.

06:28.333 --> 06:30.250
- [groaning]

06:28.333 --> 06:30.250
Ugh, what does that do?

06:30.291 --> 06:32.000
- Makes us laugh.

06:32.041 --> 06:34.125
[boys laugh]

06:34.166 --> 06:35.959
- Now, real Step One...

06:34.166 --> 06:35.959
- [groans]

06:36.000 --> 06:38.750
- You need to master the art

06:36.000 --> 06:38.750
of hiding your symptoms.

06:38.792 --> 06:40.542
If you cough,

06:38.792 --> 06:40.542
turn it into a laugh.

06:40.583 --> 06:43.125
Like this...

06:40.583 --> 06:43.125
[coughs]

06:43.166 --> 06:44.375
[laughs]

06:44.417 --> 06:46.250
Step Two:

06:46.291 --> 06:47.417
If you sound stuffed up,

06:47.458 --> 06:49.208
just pretend

06:47.458 --> 06:49.208
you smell something bad

06:49.250 --> 06:50.917
and blame it on Dicky.

06:50.959 --> 06:53.917
- Oh, if it helps,

06:50.959 --> 06:53.917
I can arrange it so you don't

06:50.959 --> 06:53.917
have to pretend.

06:53.959 --> 06:56.000
- Yeah, that's all right.

06:53.959 --> 06:56.000
Thanks.

06:56.041 --> 06:58.166
- Now, Step Three:

06:56.041 --> 06:58.166
What you nee--

06:58.208 --> 07:00.375
[all groan]

06:58.208 --> 07:00.375
Aw, Dicky.

07:00.417 --> 07:02.417
- What?

07:00.417 --> 07:02.417
Just trying to help.

07:02.458 --> 07:04.250
- Ugh, dude.

07:04.291 --> 07:07.125
[upbeat music]

07:09.000 --> 07:11.291
- Oh, hey, Mae's mom should be

07:09.000 --> 07:11.291
here any minute to pick us up.

07:11.333 --> 07:14.291
- Okay, but you still have

07:11.333 --> 07:14.291
to get past the final step:

07:14.333 --> 07:15.542
Mom's good-bye hug.

07:15.583 --> 07:18.333
The trick is,

07:15.583 --> 07:18.333
don't let her get in too tight.

07:18.375 --> 07:20.417
- Yeah.

07:18.375 --> 07:20.417
Aw, here comes the hugger.

07:20.458 --> 07:23.625
- Aww, my little babies

07:20.458 --> 07:23.625
are going

07:23.667 --> 07:26.291
on their big overnight trip.

07:26.333 --> 07:27.959
- Looks like she's bringing

07:26.333 --> 07:27.959
her A-game.

07:28.000 --> 07:29.166
- Yeah.

07:28.000 --> 07:29.166
- Come here.

07:29.208 --> 07:31.000
Come on.

07:31.041 --> 07:33.500
Come on--hey, Dawn...

07:31.041 --> 07:33.500
[grunts]

07:33.542 --> 07:37.291
Okay, this is not a hug.

07:33.542 --> 07:37.291
Come here.

07:37.333 --> 07:39.625
This is a hug.

07:39.667 --> 07:41.125
Mm.

07:41.166 --> 07:43.250
Oh, you feel warm.

07:43.291 --> 07:44.500
You're not getting sick,

07:43.291 --> 07:44.500
are you?

07:44.542 --> 07:46.000
- No.

07:46.041 --> 07:47.959
- You sound a little congested.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.166
- I'm fine.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.166
Ugh, Dicky.

07:50.208 --> 07:53.333
- Okay, you know, there is

07:50.208 --> 07:53.333
a nasty bug going around.

07:53.375 --> 07:54.959
I better take your temperature.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.208
Here.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.208
- [mumbles]

07:56.250 --> 07:57.625
- You had that in your pocket?

07:57.667 --> 07:59.166
- Yeah, that's why it's called

07:59.208 --> 08:02.041
a ther-mom-eter.

07:59.208 --> 08:02.041
[chuckles]

08:02.083 --> 08:04.917
- Uh, Mom, you better double

08:02.083 --> 08:04.917
check Dicky's overnight bag.

08:04.959 --> 08:07.000
He could have forgotten

08:04.959 --> 08:07.000
his underwear.

08:07.041 --> 08:08.500
- Or he could have packed

08:07.041 --> 08:08.500
only underwear.

08:08.542 --> 08:10.500
- You never know

08:08.542 --> 08:10.500
which way this guy's gonna go.

08:10.542 --> 08:12.583
- You're right.

08:12.625 --> 08:14.375
- What do we do?

08:14.417 --> 08:16.542
- Put that in your mouth.

08:14.417 --> 08:16.542
- No, I'm not getting sick.

08:16.583 --> 08:19.041
- I'm not getting sick either.

08:19.083 --> 08:20.500
[grunts]

08:20.542 --> 08:22.959
[dog whimpers]

08:24.291 --> 08:26.083
- Hmm, Dicky's actually got

08:26.125 --> 08:28.083
a pretty good

08:26.125 --> 08:28.083
underwear to clothes ration.

08:28.125 --> 08:29.208
[thermometer beeps]

08:31.709 --> 08:34.208
- [mouthing]

08:31.709 --> 08:34.208
- Epic moment.

08:35.417 --> 08:38.542
- Okay, let's take a look.

08:38.583 --> 08:39.959
[clears throat]

08:41.125 --> 08:43.250
Ah, normal...

08:41.125 --> 08:43.250
[chuckles]

08:43.291 --> 08:46.333
But you do have

08:43.291 --> 08:46.333
a touch of puppy breath.

08:46.375 --> 08:49.291
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

08:49.333 --> 08:52.208
<i>- ♪ La la la la la ♪</i>

08:49.333 --> 08:52.208
<i>♪ La la la la la la ♪</i>

08:52.250 --> 08:54.083
- This is it, guys.

08:52.250 --> 08:54.083
[sniffles]

08:54.125 --> 08:55.333
[sighs]

08:54.125 --> 08:55.333
We've been dreaming

08:55.375 --> 08:57.333
about this trip

08:55.375 --> 08:57.333
since first grade.

08:57.375 --> 08:59.041
- Hey, Harpers,

08:59.083 --> 09:01.125
there's a contest to guess

08:59.083 --> 09:01.125
who the epic moment

09:01.166 --> 09:02.583
is gonna happen to.

09:01.166 --> 09:02.583
You want in?

09:02.625 --> 09:04.083
- Uh, of course we want in.

09:04.125 --> 09:06.041
- Everybody's putting in

09:04.125 --> 09:06.041
their best snacks.

09:06.083 --> 09:07.667
Winner takes all.

09:07.709 --> 09:10.250
- I'm in,

09:07.709 --> 09:10.250
and I will be taking all.

09:11.834 --> 09:14.083
- Oh, hey, who'd you guys pick?

09:11.834 --> 09:14.083
- Oscar.

09:14.125 --> 09:17.250
There's a lot of places

09:14.125 --> 09:17.250
he could stick his head.

09:21.250 --> 09:22.583
- I went with Mae and Molly.

09:22.625 --> 09:24.291
They've been having

09:22.625 --> 09:24.291
some drama lately.

09:24.333 --> 09:27.583
It's been really bad.

09:27.625 --> 09:30.083
I can't wait!

09:30.125 --> 09:32.458
- All right, everyone,

09:30.125 --> 09:32.458
here comes our tour guide,

09:32.500 --> 09:35.208
so get with your buddies.

09:35.250 --> 09:38.333
- Hey, everyone, I'm Pamela,

09:35.250 --> 09:38.333
and I'd like to welcome you

09:38.375 --> 09:40.125
to the history museum.

09:40.166 --> 09:43.291
You know, I took this same trip

09:40.166 --> 09:43.291
when I was your age.

09:43.333 --> 09:47.333
[chuckles]

09:43.333 --> 09:47.333
And now I work here.

09:47.375 --> 09:49.250
- [singsong]

09:47.375 --> 09:49.250
Epic moment here we come.

09:49.291 --> 09:50.709
- Nothing can stop us now.

09:50.750 --> 09:53.417
- [sneezes]

09:50.750 --> 09:53.417
- Bless you.

09:53.458 --> 09:56.125
- Who was that?

09:53.458 --> 09:56.125
- No more "Bless yous."

09:56.166 --> 09:58.291
If any of you are sick,

09:56.166 --> 09:58.291
fess up now

09:58.333 --> 10:00.250
so your parents

09:58.333 --> 10:00.250
can come get you.

10:00.291 --> 10:01.792
There's a nasty bug

10:00.291 --> 10:01.792
that's going around,

10:01.834 --> 10:04.125
and my Gram-Gram's 90th birthday

10:01.834 --> 10:04.125
is coming up,

10:04.166 --> 10:07.208
and I will not miss it.

10:07.250 --> 10:09.542
She's having a petting zoo.

10:10.709 --> 10:13.625
[sniffing]

10:14.750 --> 10:17.500
I smell puppy breath.

10:18.625 --> 10:21.250
- [sniffles]

10:26.667 --> 10:29.250
- Well, well, well,

10:29.291 --> 10:32.375
